wikipedia.org\/wiki\/X-ray_crystallography\" title=\"X-ray crystallography\">analysis<\/a> of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Crystal_structure\" title=\"Crystal structure\">crystal structure<\/a> by means of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/X-ray\" title=\"X-ray\">X-ray<\/a>\"<\/i><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/William_Lawrence_Bragg#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> an important step in the development of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/X-ray_crystallography\" title=\"X-ray crystallography\">X-ray crystallography<\/a>.<\/p><p>Bragg was <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Knight_bachelor\" title=\"Knight bachelor\" class=\"mw-redirect\">knighted<\/a> in 1941.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/William_Lawrence_Bragg#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> As of 2014, Lawrence Bragg is the youngest ever <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Laureate\" title=\"Nobel Laureate\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Nobel Laureate<\/a> in physics, having received the award at the age of 25 years.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/William_Lawrence_Bragg#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> (The youngest of all Nobel Laureates is <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Malala_Yousafzai\" title=\"Malala Yousafzai\">Malala Yousafzai<\/a> in 2014 at the age of 17) Bragg was the director of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cavendish_Laboratory\" title=\"Cavendish Laboratory\">Cavendish Laboratory<\/a>, Cambridge, when the discovery of the structure of DNA was reported by <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/James_D._Watson\" title=\"James D. Watson\" class=\"mw-redirect\">James D. Watson<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Francis_Crick\" title=\"Francis Crick\">Francis Crick<\/a> in February 1953.<\/p>","name":"William Lawrence Bragg","place_of_birth":"North Adelaide , South Australia","place_of_death":"Waldringfield , Suffolk, England","text":"William Lawrence Bragg ,  born in Australia , Physics, 1915","year":1915.0}